body_content.explanation: a food product made of one or more types of cheese mixed together with oil, artificial colour, and salt:
examples: Processed cheese is sometimes sold in blocks or spray cans, but it is more often sold in individual slices, each in a plastic wrapper.
Pasteurized process cheese can be made from a single cheese or a blend of several cheeses.
This is a soft, creamy processed cheese product that melts more easily than other cheeses.
